    Ensembl REST API Coverage

    api_coverage.Rmd
    Endpoint ensemblr API Description
    Archive
    GET archive/id/:id TODO Uses the given identifier to return its latest version
    POST archive/id TODO Retrieve the latest version for a set of identifiers
    Comparative Genomics
    GET cafe/genetree/id/:id TODO Retrieves a cafe tree of the gene tree using the gene tree stable identifier
    GET cafe/genetree/member/id/:id TODO Retrieves the cafe tree of the gene tree that contains the gene / transcript / translation stable identifier
    GET cafe/genetree/member/symbol/:species/:symbol TODO Retrieves the cafe tree of the gene tree that contains the gene identified by a symbol
    GET family/id/:id TODO Retrieves a family information using the family stable identifier
    GET family/member/id/:id TODO Retrieves the information for all the families that contains the gene / transcript / translation stable identifier
    GET family/member/symbol/:species/:symbol TODO Retrieves the information for all the families that contains the gene identified by a symbol
    GET genetree/id/:id TODO Retrieves a gene tree for a gene tree stable identifier
    GET genetree/member/id/:id TODO Retrieves the gene tree that contains the gene / transcript / translation stable identifier
    GET genetree/member/symbol/:species/:symbol TODO Retrieves the gene tree that contains the gene identified by a symbol
    GET alignment/region/:species/:region TODO Retrieves genomic alignments as separate blocks based on a region and species
    GET homology/id/:id TODO Retrieves homology information (orthologs) by Ensembl gene id
    GET homology/symbol/:species/:symbol TODO Retrieves homology information (orthologs) by symbol
    Cross References
    GET xrefs/symbol/:species/:symbol TODO Looks up an external symbol and returns all Ensembl objects linked to it. This can be a display name for a gene/transcript/translation, a synonym or an externally linked reference. If a gene’s transcript is linked to the supplied symbol the service will return both gene and transcript (it supports transient links).
    GET xrefs/id/:id TODO Perform lookups of Ensembl Identifiers and retrieve their external references in other databases
    GET xrefs/name/:species/:name TODO Performs a lookup based upon the primary accession or display label of an external reference and returning the information we hold about the entry
    EQTL
    GET eqtl/stable_id/:species/:stable_id TODO Returns the p-value for each SNP in a given gene (e.g. ENSG00000227232)
    GET eqtl/variant_name/:species/:variant_name TODO Returns the p-values for a SNP (e.g. rs123)
    GET eqtl/tissue/:species/ TODO Returns all tissues currently available in the DB
    Information
    GET info/analysis/:species TODO List the names of analyses involved in generating Ensembl data.
    GET info/assembly/:species TODO List the currently available assemblies for a species, along with toplevel sequences, chromosomes and cytogenetic bands.
    GET info/assembly/:species/:region_name TODO Returns information about the specified toplevel sequence region for the given species.
    GET info/biotypes/:species TODO List the functional classifications of gene models that Ensembl associates with a particular species. Useful for restricting the type of genes/transcripts retrieved by other endpoints.
    GET info/biotypes/groups/:group/:object_type TODO Without argument the list of available biotype groups is returned. With :group argument provided, list the properties of biotypes within that group. Object type (gene or transcript) can be provided for filtering.
    GET info/biotypes/name/:name/:object_type TODO List the properties of biotypes with a given name. Object type (gene or transcript) can be provided for filtering.
    GET info/compara/methods TODO List all compara analyses available (an analysis defines the type of comparative data).
    GET info/compara/species_sets/:method TODO List all collections of species analysed with the specified compara method.
    GET info/comparas TODO Lists all available comparative genomics databases and their data release. DEPRECATED: use info/genomes/division instead.
    GET info/data get_data_versions() Shows the data releases available on this REST server. May return more than one release (unfrequent non-standard Ensembl configuration).
    GET info/eg_version TODO Returns the Ensembl Genomes version of the databases backing this service
    GET info/external_dbs/:species TODO Lists all available external sources for a species.
    GET info/divisions get_divisions() Get list of all Ensembl divisions for which information is available
    GET info/genomes/:genome_name TODO Find information about a given genome
    GET info/genomes/accession/:accession TODO Find information about genomes containing a specified INSDC accession
    GET info/genomes/assembly/:assembly_id TODO Find information about a genome with a specified assembly
    GET info/genomes/division/:division_name TODO Find information about all genomes in a given division. May be large for Ensembl Bacteria.
    GET info/genomes/taxonomy/:taxon_name TODO Find information about all genomes beneath a given node of the taxonomy
    GET info/ping TODO Checks if the service is alive.
    GET info/rest get_rest_version() Shows the current version of the Ensembl REST API.
    GET info/software get_software_version() Shows the current version of the Ensembl API used by the REST server.
    GET info/species get_species() Lists all available species, their aliases, available adaptor groups and data release.
    GET info/variation/:species TODO List the variation sources used in Ensembl for a species.
    GET info/variation/consequence_types TODO Lists all variant consequence types.
    GET info/variation/populations/:species:/:population_name TODO List all individuals for a population from a species
    GET info/variation/populations/:species get_populations() List all populations for a species
    Linkage Disequilibrium
    GET ld/:species/:id/:population_name get_ld_variants_by_window() Computes and returns LD values between the given variant and all other variants in a window centered around the given variant. The window size is set to 500 kb.
    GET ld/:species/pairwise/:id1/:id2 get_ld_variants_by_pair() Computes and returns LD values between the given variants.
    GET ld/:species/region/:region/:population_name get_ld_variants_by_range() Computes and returns LD values between all pairs of variants in the defined region.
    Lookup
    GET lookup/id/:id TODO Find the species and database for a single identifier e.g. gene, transcript, protein
    POST lookup/id TODO Find the species and database for several identifiers. IDs that are not found are returned with no data.
    GET lookup/symbol/:species/:symbol TODO Find the species and database for a symbol in a linked external database
    POST lookup/symbol/:species/:symbol TODO Find the species and database for a set of symbols in a linked external database. Unknown symbols are omitted from the response.
    Mapping
    GET map/cdna/:id/:region TODO Convert from cDNA coordinates to genomic coordinates. Output reflects forward orientation coordinates as returned from the Ensembl API.
    GET map/cds/:id/:region TODO Convert from CDS coordinates to genomic coordinates. Output reflects forward orientation coordinates as returned from the Ensembl API.
    GET map/:species/:asm_one/:region/:asm_two TODO Convert the co-ordinates of one assembly to another
    GET map/translation/:id/:region TODO Convert from protein (translation) coordinates to genomic coordinates. Output reflects forward orientation coordinates as returned from the Ensembl API.
    Ontologies and Taxonomy
    GET ontology/ancestors/:id TODO Reconstruct the entire ancestry of a term from is_a and part_of relationships
    GET ontology/ancestors/chart/:id TODO Reconstruct the entire ancestry of a term from is_a and part_of relationships.
    GET ontology/descendants/:id TODO Find all the terms descended from a given term. By default searches are conducted within the namespace of the given identifier
    GET ontology/id/:id TODO Search for an ontological term by its namespaced identifier
    GET ontology/name/:name TODO Search for a list of ontological terms by their name
    GET taxonomy/classification/:id TODO Return the taxonomic classification of a taxon node
    GET taxonomy/id/:id TODO Search for a taxonomic term by its identifier or name
    GET taxonomy/name/:name TODO Search for a taxonomic id by a non-scientific name
    Overlap
    GET overlap/id/:id TODO Retrieves features (e.g. genes, transcripts, variants and more) that overlap a region defined by the given identifier.
    GET overlap/region/:species/:region TODO Retrieves features (e.g. genes, transcripts, variants and more) that overlap a given region.
    GET overlap/translation/:id TODO Retrieve features related to a specific Translation as described by its stable ID (e.g. domains, variants).
    Phenotype annotations
    GET /phenotype/accession/:species/:accession TODO Return phenotype annotations for genomic features given a phenotype ontology accession
    GET /phenotype/gene/:species/:gene TODO Return phenotype annotations for a given gene.
    GET /phenotype/region/:species/:region TODO Return phenotype annotations that overlap a given genomic region.
    GET /phenotype/term/:species/:term TODO Return phenotype annotations for genomic features given a phenotype ontology term
    Regulation
    GET regulatory/species/:species/microarray/:microarray/vendor/:vendor TODO Returns information about a specific microarray
    GET regulatory/species/:species/epigenome TODO Returns information about all epigenomes available for the given species
    GET species/:species/binding_matrix/:binding_matrix_stable_id/ TODO Return the specified binding matrix
    GET regulatory/species/:species/microarray TODO Returns information about all microarrays available for the given species
    GET regulatory/species/:species/microarray/:microarray/probe/:probe TODO Returns information about a specific probe from a microarray
    GET regulatory/species/:species/microarray/:microarray/probe_set/:probe_set TODO Returns information about a specific probe_set from a microarray
    GET regulatory/species/:species/id/:id TODO Returns a RegulatoryFeature given its stable ID (e.g. ENSR00000006733)
    Sequence
    GET sequence/id/:id TODO Request multiple types of sequence by stable identifier. Supports feature masking and expand options.
    POST sequence/id TODO Request multiple types of sequence by a stable identifier list.
    GET sequence/region/:species/:region TODO Returns the genomic sequence of the specified region of the given species. Supports feature masking and expand options.
    POST sequence/region/:species TODO Request multiple types of sequence by a list of regions.
    Transcript Haplotypes
    GET transcript_haplotypes/:species/:id TODO Computes observed transcript haplotype sequences based on phased genotype data
    Variation
    GET variant_recoder/:species/:id TODO Translate a variant identifier, HGVS notation or genomic SPDI notation to all possible variant IDs, HGVS and genomic SPDI
    POST variant_recoder/:species TODO Translate a list of variant identifiers, HGVS notations or genomic SPDI notations to all possible variant IDs, HGVS and genomic SPDI
    GET variation/:species/:id TODO Uses a variant identifier (e.g. rsID) to return the variation features including optional genotype, phenotype and population data
    GET variation/:species/pmcid/:pmcid TODO Fetch variants by publication using PubMed Central reference number (PMCID)
    GET variation/:species/pmid/:pmid TODO Fetch variants by publication using PubMed reference number (PMID)
    POST variation/:species/ TODO Uses a list of variant identifiers (e.g. rsID) to return the variation features including optional genotype, phenotype and population data
    Variation GA4GH
    GET ga4gh/beacon TODO Return Beacon information
    GET ga4gh/beacon/query TODO Return the Beacon response for allele information
    POST ga4gh/beacon/query TODO Return the Beacon response for allele information
    GET ga4gh/features/:id TODO Return the GA4GH record for a specific sequence feature given its identifier
    POST ga4gh/features/search TODO Return a list of sequence annotation features in GA4GH format
    POST ga4gh/callsets/search TODO Return a list of sets of genotype calls for specific samples in GA4GH format
    GET ga4gh/callsets/:id TODO Return the GA4GH record for a specific CallSet given its identifier
    POST ga4gh/datasets/search TODO Return a list of datasets in GA4GH format
    GET ga4gh/datasets/:id TODO Return the GA4GH record for a specific dataset given its identifier
    POST ga4gh/featuresets/search TODO Return a list of feature sets in GA4GH format
    GET ga4gh/featuresets/:id TODO Return the GA4GH record for a specific featureSet given its identifier
    GET ga4gh/variants/:id TODO Return the GA4GH record for a specific variant given its identifier.
    POST ga4gh/variantannotations/search TODO Return variant annotation information in GA4GH format for a region on a reference sequence
    POST ga4gh/variants/search TODO Return variant call information in GA4GH format for a region on a reference sequence
    POST ga4gh/variantsets/search TODO Return a list of variant sets in GA4GH format
    GET ga4gh/variantsets/:id TODO Return the GA4GH record for a specific VariantSet given its identifier
    POST ga4gh/references/search TODO Return a list of reference sequences in GA4GH format
    GET ga4gh/references/:id TODO Return data for a specific reference in GA4GH format by id
    POST ga4gh/referencesets/search TODO Return a list of reference sets in GA4GH format
    GET ga4gh/referencesets/:id TODO Return data for a specific reference set in GA4GH format
    POST ga4gh/variantannotationsets/search TODO Return a list of annotation sets in GA4GH format
    GET ga4gh/variantannotationsets/:id TODO Return meta data for a specific annotation set in GA4GH format
    VEP
    GET vep/:species/hgvs/:hgvs_notation TODO Fetch variant consequences based on a HGVS notation
    POST vep/:species/hgvs TODO Fetch variant consequences for multiple HGVS notations
    GET vep/:species/id/:id TODO Fetch variant consequences based on a variant identifier
    POST vep/:species/id TODO Fetch variant consequences for multiple ids
    GET vep/:species/region/:region/:allele/ TODO Fetch variant consequences
    POST vep/:species/region TODO Fetch variant consequences for multiple regions
